8:
I'm coming, I'm coming!
...Always the troublemakers, those 
three.
16: You're here! Thank you for coming.
20:
This must be the odd yokai you 
mentioned. 
She certainly doesn't look like the 
average yokai.
23:
I've never seen any like her—
in the West OR East.
26:
She must've come here from 
another world. I can see why you 
called for me.
32:
A child, by the looks of her...
I believe she may be from the Garden 
of the Sprites.
35:
Izumiii! 
Are you gonna exorcise her?
40:
No, I will not be exorcising her. 
You can relax too, Mizuchi.
48:
I'll use the shikigami to lure her to the 
World Flipper.
50:
I'm sure her real mother must be 
worried.
61:
Now then, Mizuchi and I should start 
heading back.
62:
You're the same as ever, though. 
I was under the impression She of Nine 
Tails doesn't want yokai mingling with 
humans.
65:
Oh, I don't know what you're talking 
about, dearie. WE report to the 
princess, now don't we?
68:
Yeah! We can play with whoever we 
want!
72:
How convenient.
I guess I won't get in too much trouble, 
either, as long as we're "working" 
together.
74:
It's been increasingly difficult to hide 
our meetings from the shogunate, so 
I'd appreciate a little stealth from you, 
if nothing else.
80: Wait. Might I have a moment, diviner?
86:
Seeing you send off the little yokai to 
her mother got me wondering. 
How are your parents doing, dearie?
89:
I wonder...
I know neither their names nor faces.
91:
I was found abandoned near a small 
spring. 
My talent for the supernatural arts led 
many to suspect I may have some 
yokai blood in me.
93:
I was always told growing up that 
I must be the child of tengu. 
If that truly is the case, I'm sure they're 
in good health.
96: I see... I'm sorry for prying.
100:
Don't be. There's nothing strange or 
untoward about being an orpha—
105: Wh-what's that?! A present? But why?
109:
Oh, it's just a little gift from Milady—
for all your hard work, diviner dearie.
112:
"Milady?" 
You mean She of Nine Tails?
I seem to recall you saying just a 
moment ago that you report to her 
daughter.
115:
Goodness, child, she's my charge's 
MOTHER! 
I can run an errand or two for her!
118:
I-I see...
I wouldn't dare scorn a gift from the 
queen of yokai, though. 
I would be glad to accept it.
121:
A protective charm and... A baby's 
smock?
123:
Ahaha, humans must seem young 
to yokai. 
However I'm a little old for a smock.
126:
That's all right, dearie, 
you just hold on to it. 
It's of no use to a fox, but you may find 
it handy someday.
129:
It would be an honor to one day dress 
a child of my own in it. 
Thank you, and please pass along my 
gratitude to She of Nine Tails.
133: Well, Milady? Was that all right?
135:
He's not Seimei.
It's been centuries since Seimei was 
born—no human lives that long.
137:
I know that, but... it was about time 
I did something with his old things.
140:
Milady...
Oh? Who have we here?
143:
Ah, I remember you. 
The diviner child's attendant.
151:
Agreed. 
The both of them are, aren't they?
